    "image" : "images/Oven-Baked-Sea-Bass2.jpg",
    "ingredients" : "<ul><li>1 sea bass (1 to 2 lbs)</li><li>1 piece medium potato, chopped</li><li>1/2 piece lemon, thinly sliced</li><li>1/2 tablespoon lemon juice</li><li>1 pc sili</li><li>1 large shallot, sliced</li><li>rosemary</li><li>olive oil</li><li>salt and pepper</li></ul>",
    "instruction" : "<ol><li>Pre-heat the oven to 190C.</li><li>Cut a sheet of Aluminum foil into two large squares and place shiny side down.</li><li>Lightly brush with olive oil then place the fish in the middle of each square.</li><li>Cut two or three slashes in the flesh, season with salt and pepper then sprinkle over the rosemary.</li><li>Fold the sides of the foil up a little then pour over the lemon juice and add the shallots.</li><li>Place the chop chili on top and the lemon wedges and potato then fold the foil over to make a parcel, leaving a little air space.</li><li>Place in the oven for 20-30 minutes</li><li>Serve.</li></ol>"
